# Artifacts — training outputs, dry-run data, intermediate files
artifacts/*
# EXCEPT trained model binaries — these are code dependencies (runtime pipeline
# loads them via LIP_C1_MODEL_DIR + LIP_C2_MODEL_PATH, Dockerfile.c2/c7 bake
# them into images, tests assert on them). Small (~8MB total), signed via
# HMAC sidecars, and deterministic-enough to belong in git. Regeneration
# requires GPU + 20min + matching Optuna/torch versions, so committing them
# is the reproducibility floor.
#   Rationale history: the original "NEVER commit artifacts/" rule pre-dated
#   the signed-artifact contract introduced in 2026-04. Keeping training
#   corpora + intermediate outputs gitignored is still correct; trained
#   binaries are now a different category.
!artifacts/c1_trained/
!artifacts/c2_trained/
# Training corpora + intermediate outputs stay gitignored (regenerable from
# seed; too large for git).
artifacts/training_corpus_*/
artifacts/production_data_*/
artifacts/intermediate_*/
artifacts/synthetic/

# CIPHER: AML corpus must never be committed (contains typology patterns)
# Generate fresh with: python -m lip.dgen.generate_all --output-dir artifacts/synthetic
**/c6_corpus_*.json
**/c6_corpus_*.json.sha256
.env
.env.local
.secrets/

# MLflow local tracking database
mlflow.db
mlruns/

